* The 2012 conference, "4PLAY: Gamifuckation and Its Discontents" dealt with sex, technology and games.<ref>[http://killscreendaily.com/articles/interviews/stories-about-orcs-and-rape-man-behind-arse-elektronika/ Interview with Arse Elektronika curator Johannes Grenzfurthner in Kill Screen Magazine]: "Stories about orcs and rape: the man behind Arse Elektronika"</ref>
* The 2013 conference, "id/entity" dealt with sex, technology and identity.{{Citation needed|date=August 2018}}
* The 2014 conference, "TRANS*.*" dealt with technology and sexuality in societal and personal transition.{{Citation needed|date=August 2018}}
* The 2015 conference, "Spread Your Workload" dealt with technology and sexuality and work (tech and sex work; work and labour politics in context of sex tech; work in a physical context).{{Citation needed|date=August 2018}}
